D.q[5224] = "No? I thought so. Well, no problems... I\'ll carry on with the next step. Go and see Divad in the tower and ask him what you asked Kaffen, but make sure you tell him that I\'ll execute Kalfen if he dares refuse.";
D.q[2880] = "Greetings, milord.\n\nSuch a nice day for catching wandering souls, isn\'t it?\n\nHow may I help you?";
D.q[5704] = "Noooo!!! You stupid idiot! You Gobball intestine! You Bwork horn! You piece of Kralove dung!";
D.q[4451] = "Nooo, please! I beg of you, don\'t kill me. I\'m not a Bontarian, I work here for the money, that\'s all!";
D.q[3000] = "Not always, but most of the time! Each creature is able to bring you items, like a lining or a pair of boots, or resources or leather or amber etc. All these finds have considerable market value...and if you\'re lucky you\'ll find a guildalogem! This stone will allow you to create your own guild... If you want to learn more about this subject, go to the Guild Temple...";
D.q[5028] = "Not Dreggon people can not come. Dreggon costume not work. Other idiot tried before. \nLeave.";
D.q[2877] = "You passed the ordeal, adventurer! The Forest awaits you!";
D.q[29] = "Hello, I\'m Bowisse, the most renowned shoemaker in the Province...and the Grand Master of the Order of the Kicked Ass, a martial speciality of the shoemakers of Amakna.";
D.q[2907] = "Nice one, mercenary!";
D.q[6493] = "You want to escort the convoy? Well, that\'s very nice of you, we\'re always happy to take on volunteers, but I hope you know we can\'t pay. I already have plenty of brave soldiers who are prepared to work for... well, not much. You\'ll be following us and making sure that nothing unexpected happens. Oh and by the way, the soldiers are forbidden from talking during the trip, so don\'t go bothering them, ok. You\'ll go up front, then you won\'t have a chance to waste our time.";
D.q[2909] = "Ah big shrew! Well done!";
D.q[922] = "Not bad at all! I see you\'ve pulled a hair out of that big swine... What a jerk! I don\'t know what to do with him. Apart from showing off, he can\'t do much. If he gets beaten by the first beggar that comes along, he\'ll be dead meat if he faces the soldiers of Brakmar...";
D.q[2936] = "Dark Vlad will come back from the dead in about #1 minutes!";
D.q[2939] = "Give the key and enter.";
D.q[6400] = "Is this a Bwork recipe? I had no idea Bworks knew how to make bread. I guess it tastes as bad as it sounds, too.";
D.q[296] = "I can only offer you White Flour. Edrige uses it as a foundation, but you can also make very nice bread rolls with it. A unit of White Flour for some Mint Jelly, that\'s a fair deal, isn\'t it?";
D.q[2959] = "I now declare you free... divorced, I now declare you divorced.";
D.q[2712] = "The more we know about them, the better we are!";
D.q[2975] = "(Humming) In the port of Madrestam, the sailors sing...";
D.q[2970] = "I\'m listening...";
D.q[299] = "I asked you for 4 Boar Hairs and 2 Tusks. You think I\'m abusing my powers? Well, you\'re dead right!";
D.q[3796] = "Not only am I the most beautiful creature on Incarnam, I\'m also the most powerful. Hot and dangerous. Oh yeah!";
D.q[3582] = "Not white, albinos! Other Goblins say white louse or globule. Me ashamed. Me good. Them throw stones to me.";
D.q[1088] = "Nothing for the moment. Tonight, I\'ll put in a word for you at the meeting of the three heads.\nI\'m granting you a full day\'s leave. Take the opportunity to go wild in the taverns, you deserve it.";
D.q[1076] = "Nothing to report Sir!";
D.q[6546] = "Nothing to report for the moment. It\'s not surprising since we\'ve just come from the front outpost.";
D.q[6741] = "Nothing to report for the moment.";
D.q[6494] = "Nothing to report? You were wrong to worry after all, then, weren\'t you. I told you so, didn\'t I. \nWhat? Oh no... let\'s get the **** out of here!";
D.q[6609] = "Waa, that\'s not cool. If I tell you what you want to know will you let me sleep? So open your ears, I won\'t say this twice, I don\'t have the energy. Sadida himself hid the spellbook in a prizzz... huh, what? Who are you... ah yes, I was telling you about... ok, you\'ll find the spellbook in a vegetal prison created by Sadida himself. He\'s a very cool guy is our god. \nHow do you get in there? Ahhh, well, chill out, don\'t get worked up. Drink a Dizbi tea, that\'ll calm your nerves. The entrance is in the Dark Treechnid Forest, yup, that\'s where it is. You don\'t look so interested anymore... you ok?";
D.q[4030] = "The recipe is not complete? But I\'ve told you everything I know...";
D.q[3025] = "Menalt\'s spirit can\'t rest in peace. His wrath disturbs the sleep of the dead... Since he\'s been buried here after the Crimson Dawn Battle, his anger is gnawing at him: his head was stolen and he wants it back! At all costs! Besides, if we, centaurs, became Perceptors, it\'s above all to find Menalt\'s missing head... I\'d prefer to find it before he does... Trust me, if he succeeds in raising an army of the living dead, we\'ll know all about it!";
D.q[2436] = "The sawmill is at the edge of the forest.";
D.q[2172] = "If I were a rich man, a very very rich man, well if I were a rich man... *singing*";
D.q[3056] = "I feel a bit peckish.";
D.q[6272] = "Now I understand better why those imbeciles haven\'t come back yet. You\'re here for revenge, is that it?";
D.q[3248] = "Now everything\'s over... Dreggons got used to the sunlight and are now inhabiting the ruins of this island. The other Dragons still live in the sanctuary and seem to feed themselves with the adventurers who turn up there...\nIf you want to venture there I can help you, I\'m sort of the master of the house...";
D.q[6315] = "Waaaahhhh! Ooops, sorry. I think I might have drunk too much after all. Put the beers down here, I\'ll drink them later. \nHere, take the keys... Well, keep up the good work, I\'ll let you take them out of the jar yourself.";
D.q[3063] = "I\'ll be able to tell everyone I helped rebuild Allister\'s Castle.";
D.q[2385] = "Are you sure you want to start a career as a Hammer smith?";
D.q[952] = "Banks are located in the West side of the city.\nYou can deposit your money there in total security, the safety devices are unfailing.";
D.q[3069] = "I can\'t wait until dinner time... Good fish, good candlelight and good company.";
D.q[3788] = "Now that wasn\'t too bad, was it? You\'re a brave little traveller, aren\'t you. All my customers get a complimentary gift. Take this, it\'ll come in handy, believe me. You need to get your strength back, child. Go and see Fattumy, and buy an Incarnam Lemonade from him. In exchange for the lemonade, I\'ll give you back all the energy you lost.";
D.q[5240] = "Waaaa... zaaaaa...";
D.q[3368] = "The warrior spirit\'s not strong in you.";
D.q[3075] = "So, did you found the beast?";
D.q[308] = "Hello, Hello! Let me introduce myself - my name is Lara Soft. I\'m a retired archaeologist. In fact, I realised that the trade of pelts and the making of furs was more profitable. All the ladies in Amakna are fond of them. I became the official fur retailer for all the society parties in Amakna and my jackets are selling like hot cakes.";
D.q[3080] = "My idea of heaven is sipping on a Pig Milk while throwing little bits of smuggler to the sharks...";
D.q[5206] = "Now that you have the statuette, you\'ll have to go and free Nilevaj from prison. We just need to find out where he\'s being held. \nGo to the Amakna Castle immediately and begin investigating there... that\'s where Nilevaj was captured.";
D.q[3088] = "*Sings* \nPut the rat poison in the cobra venom,\nSqueeze three pieces of orange in,\nThat\'ll sweeten the mixture...";
D.q[3090] = "I\'m interested in this potion. It will come in handy for my business. Here are the Kamas. I feel like a boom is coming... soon my boots will be polished with Royal Slobber.\n";
D.q[3095] = "Eyeeh!";
D.q[4796] = "Now that you say it, I did see someone following the militian. It was a Sram... the only other detail I can give you is that the guy stank of fish.";
D.q[3797] = "Now you can cast a spell or two, how about we play a little game?";
D.q[1944] = "Now this is a nice place! Shame the beer\'s not as tasty as the Feubuk. But come closer....here... I\'ve heard the innkeeper adds water to his beer. Can you believe that? I\'d be ready to pay a pretty penny to know if it\'s true...";
D.q[311] = "Hello, I\'m Frankie, at your disposal. I\'m a great potion finder. Unlike seekers or hunters, I can find whatever I want. I\'m behind the famous Ghetto Raid Potion. I\'m sure you\'ve heard of its incredible effectiveness.";
D.q[3113] = "I must keep a watch over the prisoners. Can you bring these potato bags to Bhen Neddal? He\'s in the jail at the Port of Madrestam. We need to get food to him before he starves to death. Otherwise he\'ll find a way to escape.";
D.q[849] = "Now you\'re here could you go find someone who knows how to make magic poison. There must be a person in the city who has good poisoning knowledge!";
D.q[3811] = "Now you know the deal, go find all that stuff in Incarnam. ";
D.q[5255] = "We have planned revenve for what happened in the cavern. We can\'t attack now, but we have already taken control of the territories we require to make things easier for us.";
D.q[314] = "It\'s my last stroke of inspiration...a potion even more powerful than Ghetto Raid! I know that one day, my genius will be recognised!";
D.q[1429] = "There is no potential suspect in your investigation report, you should continue your questionings...";
D.q[1860] = "Now you\'re ready for winter! Except... your ears... Now that\'s not right, is it? You need something to accentuate those pretty eyes and that jawline needs some serious underline. Trust me, I\'ve JUST what you need!";
D.q[6343] = "Now you\'re showing some signs of intelligence. Latem Sa, the incompetent fool, works for Bonta, but I\'ve already told you that. Maybe the other smiths sometimes get orders for the city. Go to Amakna and find out, that\'s my advice.";
D.q[6763] = "We\'ve succeeded. I\'m not surprised - the gods are with us after all.";
D.q[3358] = "There you go! Happy shearing!";
D.q[339] = "It\'s likely to rain, and I\'m afraid the corn grains might sprout on the spot. Reap 100 units of wheat and I\'ll give you one of my best scythes.";
D.q[1945] = "Now you\'ve got the bottles, you can give one each to the Gobballs. Be careful though, people might get jealous! Come back when you\'re done... I think I\'ll need some more help. ";
D.q[32] = "Another very busy day... I hope Farle is getting on alright with the harvest. Don\'t hesitate to go and see him if you\'re looking for work.";
D.q[2308] = "Now, by Iop, you have your own sword. Get equipped and kill two Arachnees for me! That will prove just what you\'re capable of. If I deem you worthy, I\'ll will entrust you with a mission of far greater importance.";
D.q[2360] = "Now, listen carefully... Wilde is my brother. He explains things so clearly, he\'ll have you understanding things you didn\'t know existed before you\'re finished shaking his hand! When I was a kid, he used to explain a whole lot of complicated stuff to me and I\'d understand... And this time, he told me there\'s no way we\'re moving as long as there\'s a rat around! So you go back there right now!";
D.q[4286] = "Ah, our efforts were fruitful. The Drunken Pandawa Inn, is it? We\'ll be able to contact him now.\nHere\'s a couple of beers to wet that throat of yours.";
D.q[3180] = "This an excellent question! If I were you, I\'d walk up and down this library a bit longer... you might end up meeting him.";
D.q[1394] = "We just nabbed a Bontarian on the run, heheeh! He probably thought he was safe when he saw the Sidimote Gorge. Unfortunately for him, we were there...hehehe... What? You were looking for him? Well, one of my men is taking him to the prison\'s interrogation rooms.";
D.q[1960] = "Thank you very much. I\'m going to cook that right away, stay right here, I\'m coming back with some for you. I\'m sure you\'ll like it. See you in a minute...";
D.q[4091] = "Now, we would need to go get the wedding dress in Bonta. Can you do it?";
D.q[1084] = "Now, that\'s interesting! I know a few people who\'ve earned themselves a whipping tonight, and this time I\'ll make sure they don\'t enjoy it... Well done!";
D.q[4037] = "Now, we\'d have to go to Bonta and pick up the wedding dress. Would you mind doing it?";
D.q[1097] = "This is for you, come back again when you need more.";
D.q[3207] = "You lost your way already? Hahaha! As soon as I spoke to you, I knew you would! You couldn\'t find your way out of a paper bag, could you? \nPfft, whatever. I guess I should help you get back to the slab room. Think you can manage that?";
D.q[759] = "OK #1, a little general knowledge test on the art of tactics. This way I\'ll see if you really deserve my esteem. \nIf you fail the test you\'ll be on spud-bashing again heh heh!";
D.q[2253] = "Thanks for the lemons but...t o make stewed black Gobball pudding, you need Gobball legs... Makes sense, doesn\'t it? Huh? Hurry up! I\'m getting hungry...";
D.q[5561] = "I don\'t like what I\'m hearing here... Go quickly to the alchemists\' workshop and tell Merlinmagus what\'s going on. With the help of Silvosse, it won\'t be too late.";
D.q[326] = "No one has yet penetrated the hole. My mission will continue until someone does. But... who are you ?! You\'re not Hanniboul... Leave me alone, I\'m on a very special assignment.\nOh, by the way, you wouldn\'t be looking for scrolls, would you? I\'ve some here if you\'re interested.";
D.q[2394] = "OK but before I show you the ropes, you\'ll have to do me a favour. The fishmonger has some bait for me, I need them very quickly. Here\'s the deal - bring them to me in less than 5 minutes and I\'ll teach you the tricks of the trade.";
D.q[201] = "OK, I\'ll introduce you to Wiss Catz. But please, remember not to give him any clover, he\'s on a strict diet.";
D.q[850] = "OK, all this is very nice but you must go to the East rampart. Some Bontarians are launching a massive attack there and we\'ll soon be short of Chafers. It\'s time to brandish your weapon!";
D.q[3270] = "Which profession do you want to learn?";
D.q[371] = "Very good. Bring me 70 Prespic Peaks and 70 Crab Pincers. I use them to make solid shields, decorated with peaks. Resistant, frightening and very expensive. What else could I hope for?\nOh yeah, your reward... I\'ll give you a Strength Scroll if you bring me everything I\'ve just asked you for.";
D.q[3275] = "Congratulations! You\'ve just defeated the Ancestral Treechnid as he was barely awaken. I\'m sure you\'ll show off in all Amakna tonight... Fortunately, you seem to have been spared by the curse of the Treechnid Forest. I won\'t have to put up with you any longer!";
D.q[3228] = "What? You still want to continue this discussion? I\'ve already wasted enough time with you! Besides, I\'ve told you everything I know about the Porcos!";
D.q[2282] = "Look for it and you\'ll find it! The temples are all in the province of Amakna, and those of your race will give you the information you need.";
D.q[6258] = "Of course I know him... well, not personally, but I\'ve done business with him, you know? I hunt Dragoturkeys and sell them off to Bonta militia whenever they need some. I work with Captain Starky, so you could say that I know him, yes.";
D.q[603] = "Of course I\'ve flown, several times even... I was once a bird gliding through the sky of Amakna... What a sweet dream!... I painted several canvases on the subject.";
D.q[2994] = "Of course, I knew it... Make sure that your words are being said on the right side of the star or else no one will hear you! And don\'t pollute the World\'s atmosphere with impure words. To make it short, just behave and be polite! Don\'t be like Herdegrize... the old erudite man insults others far too often. He truly hates me you know... I think he was a Gobball in a previous life. And obviously when he sees me reading their entrails, it makes him really mad...";
D.q[3267] = "Of course... If you find my son, tell him his mommy\'s looking for him!";
D.q[2164] = "Offer your services";
D.q[3341] = "Hello! Welcome to the Test Server!\n\nWhat can I do for you?";
D.q[3339] = "My, I\'m... I thought you were avoiding me... I thought you would never return. You have changed a little... and yet... Okay, excuse me, I\'m rambling again. Emmhhh... please bring me some.... ehhh... some pieces of Bloody Koalak and Brown Warko. Can you do that friend? you\'re my friend, aren\'t you? Ah yes. So please hurry...";
D.q[631] = "Oh I see, very well. I won\'t shame you with a qualification test. Being alchemist is above all a vocation, and you have amply proved your determination by travelling so much in all Amakna. Here is your Alchemist Certificate. One last piece of advice before you start: you should know that certain flowers grow everywhere whereas some others only grow in particular places. So don\'t forget to take note of the good collecting places. Good luck for what\'s to come. See you soon, colleague.";
D.q[547] = "Need eat meat. You bring 4 shells different colours and me can prepare meal. To reward meat, you can go back village and wait be next meal.";
D.q[1895] = "Oh my! It\'s the same thing every day! If I sleep for so much as a minute the whole night, I find a part of my herd slaughtered. I\'ve seen a creature in these parts that looked like a Miliboowolf, only hairier. I\'ve tried to catch it... but it\'s too fast. I wonder who might know about this. There must be someone in Astrub some sort of expert... Don\'t you think?";
D.q[2510] = "Oh my! Seems you\'re back from Astrub... I can tell from your puffy eyes... I was just thinkin\', now this is an eye that saw a lot of things and mostly that saw an Enutrof patrol being saved! Hahaha! do ya recognize me?";
D.q[3683] = "Oh no, my dear, Incarnam is a safe, peaceful place, not at all like the horrible old World of Twelve.";
D.q[4031] = "Oh yeah! Of course, Wabbit teeth! Unfortunately, I used all I had for my previous potion... Can you go and collect the ingredients, please?";
D.q[310] = "Oh yes! If you can bring me back some mouse hair, I\'ll exchange them for my stock of Gobball leather. I\'ve some left from the past season and I really don\'t know what to do with it.";
D.q[3871] = "Oh! I see you got some more information about these Rogues! Tell me what the Sram told you... a dangerous zone surrounded with water... Well, you should search over by the cemetery of Amakna";
D.q[337] = "I need help finishing the harvest.";
D.q[3381] = "Keep goin\' buddy! If ya don\' finish wha\' I told ya to do, the Master won\'t be happy.";
D.q[3873] = "Oh! Sugar! Where is this den!? I\'m late for my nap... What? You know Yse Vewybad, the minister? You can help me then! Would you mind searching for this den?";
D.q[2127] = "Oh! Is this cake for me?";
D.q[1586] = "Oh! Master Kweatssends you. Hurry, I\'m putting my life at stake to pay off this debt!\nThe card for the leaf, as planned?";
D.q[4944] = "We really beat the hell out of them, but I can\'t understand why it\'s only the younger recruits who came along. What\'s more, Oto Mustam wasn\'t there. Something\'s up... something\'s being hidden. Whatever the case, you did a good job. You can now go back to Bonta and report to Amayiro.";
D.q[3533] = "Come and see me again when you have time. If you\'d help a Goblin, surely you\'ll help a Bwork mage.";
D.q[5488] = "Oh! You lout!\nGo and learn how to talk to a lady!";
D.q[2337] = "A dark rose... hmmm, that is crazy! So, the flowers are still mutating then, and turning into more and more powerful species!\nYour information gave me an idea for an experiment... I want you to take care of it for me.\nTake these dark rose seeds and plant them in the Astrub fields, under the rock over there! Hihihihiii! We\'ll see some sparks fly.";
D.q[830] = "I\'ve appointed 5 of my best agents to carry out a special raid on Bonta... *rubs hands*... I bet you\'re wondering why? Anyhow, each of them needs a Brakmarian cloak to cover their Tabi and their crime. Bring these cloaks to me. We don\'t have time to go shopping with the psychological preparation we\'re doing.";
D.q[1336] = "Oh, I see, we\'ve been invited by Danathor to receive a medal of honour! I\'ve just remembered, we can\'t go to the ceremony without a Bontarian cloak...";
D.q[4105] = "If you use the first potion, all of your characteristics will be reset to zero. You\'ll lose any points that you gained from characteristic scrolls but you\'ll get back everything else.";
D.q[3981] = "Oh, Tofus? Ask Shika, she knows more than I do about that.";
D.q[3948] = "Oh, a Wabbit! Welcome to our castle, noble pwince!";
D.q[559] = "Finally, I suggest you visit the island\'s western side, where a magical jungle awaits. Its luxuriant flora and strange fauna will fascinate you. If you\'re lucky enough, you\'ll meet the island\'s inhabitants and discover their rich folklore, and you might even be invited to sit at their table. If you have time, try to get to the south of the island where you might have the ultimate privilege of meeting the Chief of Moon Island.";
D.q[1237] = "Oh, am I scaring you with my deadly swinging and swiping? It\'s just my daily training. Don\'t worry";
D.q[3932] = "Oh, an expert! Do you know what they asked me lately? I\'ll tell you for 10 silk strings.";
D.q[597] = "Oh, how do you know that? Yes, I flew once, I jumped from the rooftop of my house and glided more than 5 metres. The hardest part was making the wooden wings... My lumberjack uncle and a tailor friend of his put them together. I think they used 4 ash planks and 10 linen strings.";
D.q[1339] = "Oh, hi Lyeno, you\'ve lost weight, haven\'t you? The last time I saw you, you were well-padded and as stiff as a poker...";
D.q[3505] = "Alone, I\'m desperately alone among bullies and bully hunters.";
D.q[377] = "Oh, it\'s nothing too complicated... It\'s just mushroom-filled doughnut dough. It\'s really delicious and everybody seems friendly when you eat one. Look, could you bring me a hundred or so of these delicious mushrooms? I\'ll exchange them for a Small Wisdom Scroll. Since I started eating those doughnuts, I don\'t really need them any more...";
D.q[4012] = "Oh, thanks, a delivery! I shall then serve your prince, noble sir.";
D.q[2259] = "Oh, thanks a lot, I knew I could count on you... Here, take this loaf of bread, it\'ll heal your wounds...";
D.q[1507] = "Oh, there is not much you can do. You\'d better go get a bow at the Smith\'s. Unless you just want to stay back in support.";
D.q[5607] = "Oh, that\'s pure gold! Thank you. \nSo you wanted to meet a member of the Terra family? You\'re out of luck. Terra Cogita, my old friend, was captured by Bworks several years ago and I\'m sure that they\'ll have nibbled him away to nothing by now. Sorry, but I don\'t think you\'ll find anything of use over there.";
D.q[3516] = "Hum...how can I put it... hum... I\'d say... a mumussel (without fries). There are a lot on the Asse Sea beach.";
D.q[586] = "Oh, you important Great Kanniball. Nice mask. Can pass!";
D.q[3826] = "Oh, you betcha there\'s some good stuff in there. You bet. Next time you see me, if there is a next time, I\'ll be giving you a big reward for getting through the worst hellpit ever. I only give it out once.";
D.q[3192] = "Last time I saw Lord Crow, he was hiding in the ninth room, or maybe in the tenth one, or was it in the thirteenth? or the fourteenth?... Well, I don\'t remember.";
D.q[288] = "Oh... a visitor! Am I dreaming? Woohoo! Hi there! Let me introduce myself. My name is Ale One. I\'ve been living here for more than 10 years and you\'re the first visitor I\'ve seen in a very long time. I bought that land for a song at the time and now I understand why the salesman burst out laughing when I handed the money over. I\'ve been trying to sell it myself for... let\'s see... 9 years, 10 months and 17 days.";
D.q[1927] = "Thanks a million. I\'m going to be able to do the test safely now and it\'s mostly thanks to you. The apprentices and I are very grateful to you. Take this magical ring, its magical power is not yet activated but you can do that yourself!";
D.q[2300] = "Ohhh...I knew the Eniripsas were touchy but this... Anyway, thanks for trying.";
D.q[3200] = "Are you sure you want to enter this labyrinthine library? Do you have an invitation from Lord Crow or the key to his library? I hope he\'ll agree to see you. He doesn\'t like to be disturbed when he\'s reading.";
D.q[2668] = "Ohh, I\'m suffering here. My last fight almost killed me. Would you happen to have an apple? It would make me feel a lot better.";
D.q[2135] = "Thanks a lot. Please, just wait a minute... There you go, that\'s PER-FECT, you look delightful in it. Mummy always said I was talented.";
D.q[3951] = "Oh...But we were not expecting you so early...";
D.q[6239] = "Ok, I get it. I\'ll shut up. You Brakmarians are really unusual, you know that. Sometimes you even remind me of my uncle Jack who was devoured by a Whitish Fang.";
D.q[6240] = "Ok, I get it. I won\'t ask you anything else. \n...\nYou wouldn\'t have a Kama, would you? Come on, what\'s a Kama to you?";
D.q[836] = "Ok #1, let\'s have a little test on the art of treachery... we\'ll see if you\'re worthy of me.";
D.q[2205] = "Really, she told me you were coming here... Well, like a good initiate, you should try to form a bond with her. For this, Nature gives up a bit of her bounty and you have to protect it in return! Go and see Oli Venders, the Lumberjack, he probably has just what you need to make a good staff - a branch of Hurrywood. Just follow your compass. Come back to me afterwards...";
D.q[3561] = "Chief don\'t talk with the weakling!";
D.q[5661] = "Ok, I\'ll give you something to do if it\'ll keep you from bothering me. But mind yourself, it\'s top secret, you can\'t talk to anyone about it. \nSome Bontarian renegades have found out about the two statuettes that Maimane gave to Sumens. These incredibly powerful statuettes represent the good and evil in humanity so you can understand why we\'re so interested in getting our hands on them before those Bontarians. \nGo and see Setag, the Enutrof master and drag it out of him. Make sure you bring him something to make it worth his while.";
D.q[2159] = "Ok, I\'ve done the blood test... Go and talk to Saketsu, he\'ll explain everything to you...";
D.q[357] = "Hello! My name\'s Lee Aibig. I\'m an old farmer and the more time that passes, the older I get. All I can manage to swallow these days is soup. Acorn soup is my favourite. Bring me the ingredients I need and I\'ll give you some Agility scrolls in return. As you can imagine, I don\'t need them anymore... The last time I used one, I just lay on my bed for the day, trying to take my pants off over my head.";
D.q[4461] = "Ok, at least we\'ve one ally in Bonta, that could prove very useful to us.\nYou\'ve got nothing to do now? Good. That means you can go back to Bonta and find out the secret to taming Whitish Fangs. If you don\'t know where to start, you might as well go to the library.";
D.q[5556] = "Ok, fine, I\'ll help you out. \nThere actually is a spell called Transgenesis, but it takes a long time to prepare. I\'ll also need the right ingredients, and plenty of peace and quiet.\nSo I\'m going to need 40 Pandkin Seeds, 20 Poppy Seeds, 20 units of Magical Cure, 10 Ambusher Buds and 2 units of Vampiric Liquid.";
D.q[3573] = "A valiant warrior, just what I need. I want you to rid the region of the terrible creatures that live there. I\'d have done it myself but I\'ve got a lot to do right now. You know, stuff, here and there, loads...";
D.q[4264] = "Ok, let\'s all take a deep breath. We\'ve all understood. If you want to find out more, get in touch with Hersa Dark Claw In Bonta... just don\'t say that we told you.";
D.q[3588] = "Hello. I don\'t have time to talk. If you want something, go and see the foreman.";
D.q[4034] = "Thanks for the ingredients. Wait a minute. I warm the water, I stir it one way, then the other. And voilà! Here\'s your potion!";
D.q[4434] = "We shouldn\'t be following Djaul! He will bring about the destruction of all living things. This is not what Brakmar stands for, you must believe me!";
D.q[1083] = "Ok, ok, I admit it! This system is totally stupid, take my word for it, we\'ll never be able to take Bonta with that kind of laws!";
D.q[4002] = "Weird? Go away before I get all worked up!";
D.q[1371] = "Ok, ok! I understood! To be frank, I didn\'t write that report. If you want one, you\'ll have to get a move on! These bones are too important to be abandoned.";
D.q[458] = "I trapped three of them while rambling through the mountains northeast of the village. I was lucky that they were timid... however it\'s also very difficult to approach them. I\'m more used to growing peas myself!";
D.q[3599] = "Every society relies on its agriculture system for which the farmers are responsible. Sowing, harvesting, maintaining the soils fertile are as many tasks that the farmers are responsible for. Being a farmer is a noble profession, it feeds numerous people. Shall I start teaching you how to harvest cereals? ";
D.q[3595] = "I like a Gob snack!";
D.q[6498] = "Ok, ok, you win, now give me back my tibia.\n...\nI don\'t know exactly what kind of trouble is brewing, but Milone Corichel the jeweller is involved in corruption dealings. Question him for more information.";
D.q[1039] = "Ok, since you want it so much...You\'ll have to kill a Gobball as fast as possible: you have two minutes. Prove you can do it and I\'ll name you hunter.";
D.q[3361] = "Ok. Bring me the six Dofus... and we\'ll see what we can do.";
D.q[1165] = "Ok, you got it, that damned paper. Can I crash out now ?";
D.q[2162] = "Ok, you managed to fill your jug, well done! Clear off now!";
D.q[1157] = "Okay, first of all, tell me this. If you meet a stranger pretending to be a Guardian of Tainela like me and he asks you the code to your house, what will your answer be?";
D.q[2138] = "Okay, getting better! So you warned everyone... Hey! Don\'t you even think about sitting down, you maggot? Go back and report to Joe Stonefiddler.";
D.q[2043] = "No hilt, no sword. Go to Oli Venders the lumberjack.";
D.q[2795] = "Okay, the time\'s come for you to go where time stood still for \'the one who we don\'t speak of.\'";
D.q[2361] = "Woh, I told you this wasn\'t an easy job and you still want to become a hunter? To handle a hunter\'s weapons, you need a certain dexterity, prove me you have what it takes and I\'ll declare you a hunter.";
D.q[3633] = "You won\'t get any Kamas here, but I can teach you some tricks that will be useful later.";
D.q[5133] = "Okay, these three disciples seem promising... especially the fat one there.\nAll I need now is a name for my latest order. I\'m happy with the work you\'ve done for me, even though you\'ve made a number of errors, so I\'m going to let you advise me on who to take.";
D.q[3754] = "Let\'s have a look in here.";
D.q[3108] = "On his last visit in the Port of Madrestam, King Allister said that even mermaids envy my beauty.";
D.q[2646] = "I think I should organise another initiatory journey pretty quickly.";
D.q[3250] = "Once inside the Dreggon Sanctuary, you\'ll be able to feel the madness that drove the disciples of Osamodas. The inside of the sanctuary resembles its occupants... it\'s grandiose, terrifying, mysterious, but mostly lethal!\nBefore you make your decision and go look for these shell fragments, I must warn you: there is a magic door in this sanctuary that leads to the room where Dreggons were made to mate...";
D.q[3713] = "One day I\'ll get up early enough and head off on my own adventure.";
D.q[3145] = "One day, our mentor, Skeunk, will punish you and your behind will be as red as... as... as... a Red Piwi!";
D.q[6346] = "Well get out of here then!";
D.q[382] = "Hi, I\'m the renowned Bolzano Vieilletrasse. You\'ve probably heard about me already. I make all sorts of strange and useful things with bits and pieces of plants and animals. I\'m working on a big project at the moment but I need materials to give free rein to my creativity.";
D.q[6245] = "One minute, I put it in the box and I can\'t find the piece of paper I wrote the combination on...";
D.q[2867] = "Stop! You can\'t go any further... The Pandikazes have sabotaged the bridge leading to the peninsula... ";
D.q[2672] = "OoOoMm Pandawa OoOoMm. *Praying.*";
D.q[4862] = "One of the slimiest creatures in Astrub, Gabmucs Yt\'rid, has just been captured. He\'s in Astrub jailhouse and I want to free him... he would make a fine recruit.";
D.q[2910] = "OoOoMm Pandawa OoOoMm - (praying)";
D.q[2811] = "Right answer, now let\'s say you have a Pandawa friend studying Earth Pandawushu and you want to get him a shield as a present, which one will suit him best? The Asse Shield, the Phtalmo, the Fire Dial or the Treechnid Shield?";
D.q[3296] = "To be honest, there were times when I seriously doubted it myself. But we finally have a building dedicated to knowledge, culture and intelligence worthy of commemorating the greatness of Bonta.";
D.q[2694] = "Oohyahooh! A friend of one of my friend\'s is a friend of mine! And all the Pandawas are my friends, so you must be a friend of mine!";
D.q[396] = "Hey there! My name is Ozen... they say I\'m a wise man, but other folk say that wise men never believe they\'re wise, so... well, in any case, I know everything there is to know about relaxing plants. At the moment, I\'m searching for many different ingredients in the quest to make the ultimate relaxation potion.";
D.q[2426] = "There are many types of carvers, one specialising in each type of weapon - staffs, wands and other wooden implements. Lots of wood and a bit of everything else are used in these trades. As with any crafting profession, you\'ll have to have a few Kamas saved up to get off the ground, but if you put in a few years of hard craft, you\'ll be putting your feet up for good before too long!";
D.q[395] = "I must make a lot and then reduce it with a magical process. For this, I\'ll need 80 Arachnee legs.";
D.q[399] = "I want to develop a new potion. I\'m gonna call it \'Polite Juice\'. I need 50 Blue Larva skins, 40 Orange Larva skins and 40 Green Larva skins.";
D.q[2587] = "Ooom Pandawa oom - Shsh! The words of the goddess are about to flutter into my sacred eardrums!";
D.q[482] = "Nobody\'s in need of a murder at the moment. Get outta here!";
D.q[1105] = "Ooooh, freeesh meat.... Don\'t worry, I\'m not talking about you! You\'re way too thin to be sold at the market. You should think of eating a little more. By the way, would you like to buy some real good meat?";
D.q[4023] = "Let me think about it in peace!";
D.q[3888] = "Ossshh, you\'re perssshhistant, that\'sssh a good ssshing...\nFollow me, ssshhh.";
D.q[1723] = "Osamodas can use any weapon, but they handle hammers and staffs best.";
D.q[1747] = "Osamodas are usually intelligent or very resistant characters but they\'re always looking for things to help them improve on these skills.";
D.q[2859] = "To get out of here, you can either pay 1,000 Kamas of bail or wait 2 minutes. \nThis jail is way too small for us to lodge such wretched creatures as you all the time...";
D.q[2236] = "Thanks for the wool... But what d\'ya want me to do without a bow?";
D.q[2295] = "Poisoned acorns...No, they\'re certainly too cunning to fall into that trap... Maybe another doll... bloody squirrels *grmbl*";
D.q[1101] = "Well, I can tell you\'re a good soul. Here, take this cannon powder... free of charge!\n";
D.q[411] = "How can I be of service to you?";
D.q[4649] = "Well, I hope you got there on time.";
D.q[5476] = "Ougaa is a minor deity with a mushroom for a head. That detail is important, believe me. It\'s said that she\'s venerated by the Porcos... and adventurers make offerings to her for reasons known only to them. Places of worship for this minor goddess are to be found on the four corners of the continent. As for me, I\'m happy staying here, trying to get passing adventurers into trouble with Ougaa. It\'s always funny to watch those fools taking the beast on.";
D.q[420] = "If you like fighting for pleasure, you can challenge other people.\nChallenges are even allowed within the village. They\'re considered as an entertainment, or even, a way of training before hunting creatures for example.";
D.q[2013] = "I knew you would like it. So let\'s have a sneak peek in the future, and to do that... What?! Cheating?!... You\'d better know, my young apprentice, that Xelors never cheat! They just often anticipate, which shows how intelligent they are! So, I was saying, I\'m going to need some ingredients: two crystal phials of pale Anthir that you\'ll get from Dragonsly, the alchemist, Epyss grain that one of the workers at the food warehouse will give you, and wood from Oli Venders\'. Simple wood, unadorned! The wood determines how far you go, and I only want to see the near future.";
D.q[6237] = "Watch out, I\'m going to cross. When we\'re done, escort me to Rigal Hookhand at the Sram temple and I\'ll give you the document on Xephires. Oh yeah, I didn\'t tell you before, but I don\'t have the information on me... haha. And if something happens in the meantime, we\'ll meet over there. \nFor now, just hold onto that rope.";
D.q[2461] = "Three-Flower? Ah yes indeed, he\'s one of our best customers! He\'s often hanging around the rivers and valleys of the Asse coast... he just loves Asse, can\'t get enough.";
D.q[3977] = "Oul people have found gloly once mole!";
D.q[3116] = "Be careful! Don\'t try to fool me or you\'ll end locked up peeling potatoes and eating cold maggot soup for the rest of your days.";
D.q[2028] = "Waatttcchhh Oouut! By the Twelve Gods. You\'re not in summer camp, young one! March onward and keep your trap shut! Ok, glory doesn\'t grow on trees, but our Enutrof friends have worked hard to hand it to us on a silver plate...";
D.q[4294] = "If he refuses, we can always threaten him.\nOr better, I\'ve a few heavies that are looking for a job at the moment.";
D.q[3330] = "Be careful! Sadida is quite touchy at the moment. He doesn\'t like people picking up his flowers. Protectors guard the precious plants.";
D.q[4298] = "Do you have the gold?";
D.q[1392] = "Be careful, you\'re approaching the Sidimote Gorge...this neck is almost the only way between Bonta and Brakmar. No surprise then if I tell you confrontations are very common here. Anyway, it\'s quiet for the moment.";
D.q[3101] = "You probably realised that everyone either wants to sell me something or see my butt. All I want is a small house where I can live peacefully with someone I love.";
D.q[4347] = "Sorry? I found something strange here!";
D.q[6706] = "You wanted to batter the leader of the burglars, but instead you got beaten yourself? Well if they\'d managed to get into the house, I\'d have laid you out for the birds... but since they didn\'t, I\'ll give you another chance to prove yourself.";
D.q[4542] = "Our arrows will pierce their ranks as fast as we can fire them. Speak to the commander to give the signal.";
D.q[4388] = "I know that resupplying a bunch of militiamen isn\'t the classiest work, but someone has to do it.";
D.q[3331] = "Well, I\'ll make it short. I need pieces of Kaliptus and Koalaks. ";
D.q[4095] = "Our beer recipe? Well, if you insist... But only Bworks can make it the right way.";
D.q[3430] = "Our children have disappeared! I was at work and when I got home I found my wife, Mrs El, crying her eyes out. It\'s been two days and I\'m sick with worry. Help us. Please, help us.";
D.q[3882] = "Well, I\'m not interested then!";
D.q[1580] = "As there\'s a river of lava between the bank and the ramparts, you should ask Mech Riorraw\'s niece to have her uncle make you a long range weapon...";
D.q[4367] = "Our convoy of Astrubian merchants was ambushed not so long ago. You must escort the next convoy and protect it if necessary. I also want you to gather information on these bandits. They could be the same ones as before.";
D.q[3053] = "Our good king Allister needs bloody Dragoturkey steaks for his table. Can you bring me some?";
D.q[3591] = "A fisherman? Well, that will make a nice change. There\'s a lot of us here, so hurry up and catch enough fish for everyone.";
D.q[3308] = "Our good King Allister entrusted me with a special mission: to create the most beautiful stud farm in the region. And I can see from your bow-legs that you\'ve ridden a mount before. Would you mind providing me with a few Dragoturkeys? The King will reward you well.";
D.q[4281] = "What?! He asked you for something and then disappeared? Idiot! It\'s a good thing I know what happened...";
D.q[1562] = "Whatever you do, please don\'t tell my parents I\'m here.";
D.q[3072] = "Out of my sight rascal! Boor! Lout!";
D.q[4665] = "Out of my way you devil. Filthy bog pirate! Scaraleaf taxidermist! Killer of Pink Piwis!\nMay Rushu make Filtounga vomit out of your ears.";
D.q[1068] = "Ouuhhh itiz youw! Diou wantee tou tolk a byt?";
D.q[2218] = "Over dere, it\'s Amakna. Dere are some weird stories about what\'s going on over dere. But I can see on your face, that you might well like dat!";
D.q[473] = "Hewe it is, now you\'ll be able to gwow cawwots youwself.";
D.q[2601] = "Pandawas are most deadly with axes and staffs. Find an axe smith or a staff carver to equip yourself and you\'ll be a happy Pandawa!";
D.q[3923] = "So, the King is marrying his niece...? Ahem... Maybe we can get a Prince on our payroll... Do you know if the princess has any other suitors?";
D.q[1132] = "Whatever... No need to discuss! A simple look at your clothes and it\'s obvious that you wouldn\'t have a clue!";
D.q[5219] = "What... an intruder?\nYou\'ll die with a scream on your face and we\'ll have you for supper.";
D.q[3073] = "The Site Chief has invited me out for another binge? Great! I\'ll drown his sorrows and his fish with beer!";
D.q[3071] = "The Site Chief? Monabella sent him packing again, didn\'t she? I\'m sick of eating fish! I\'m gonna say no!\nI\'ll take my chances, maybe I\'ll bump into someone who\'s a little more gallant, a little richer and a lot more carnivorous. Hehehe.";
D.q[2482] = "I need some Amber, what are those guys doing? Amber isn\'t that hard to find, is it ?";
D.q[3743] = "To catch bigger and bigger fish, a fisherman must regularly change his equipment.";
D.q[1109] = "People always tell me I bring bad luck to everyone I met... Do you believe you can escape the misfortune I spread?";
D.q[5150] = "I had to close the hostel for the duration of the trial. You do not realise the loss in Kamas that this closure represents.";
D.q[2617] = "Him escaped Poochan. But me tear off piece of clothes of him and find nametag: Lanma Metoasa. Poochan know father Metoasa, him live close main Dojo. If Lanma escape, me force him come. You go see father and convince he to give his son to Poochan, him respect old tradition. You take this dish with you. You understand when there.";
D.q[537] = "Hello, Dear Future Guest. You seem to be tired of all this fighting... well remember, You\'re not your job. You\'re not how many Kamas you have in the bank. You\'re not the mount you ride. You\'re not your expensive headgear. You\'re not your Gobball Set. You\'re the all-singing, all-dancing mud of the world... Well the \'A\' Tourist Team can help you. A 50% discount off our normal prices... yes, you heard me... You simply MUST take advantage of this offer!";
D.q[6316] = "What... are you looking for a fight? Let me tell you, if you hurt me, I\'ll scream and then the whole garrison will be after you.";
D.q[2677] = "Perfect! Go see one of our fabulous peddles! They have everything that pleases the goddess...";
D.q[6661] = "The main drawbacks of being aligned are related to aggression. If you\'re aligned and a militiaman of the opposing alignment attacks you, you\'ll no longer have the protection of guards if you\'re in a neutral area. Another large drawback is that the guards of opposing cities will attack you if pass too close to them and they see you. This is particularly troublesome if you want to access workshops and markets. Finally, when you\'re aligned and you\'re beaten by a militiaman or a guard of an enemy alignment, you might find yourself in jail. It\'s also impossible to use Zaaps to access areas belonging to an enemy alignment. I strongly advise you to think carefully before choosing an alignment, as it\'s not something you should take lightly. In the meantime, go earn your spurs and come back and see me when you have more experience, I may have a tip for you.";
D.q[3645] = "Where can I find good workers?";
D.q[3209] = "Perfect! You\'ve found the relics needed to enter the Minotoror Room! Come on! Follow me! I\'ll try to get you there in one piece. I\'ll just take those two relics from you, and the Minotoror Key I gave you as well. They\'ll go quite nicely towards my pension fund.";
D.q[2893] = "Ouch! My bag is way too heavy! I\'m coming back from Pandala... I got so many good deals over there! It\'s WICKED!";
D.q[2891] = "Ouch! My bag is way too heavy! But I\'m coming back from Pandala where I made some good deals! WICKED!";
D.q[1514] = "Everyone was peacefully living their lives, rediscovering the story of the protectors and gods... when suddenly, warriors from Bonta assaulted Brakmar. It was a massacre. After we repelled them, we unanimously voted to take our revenge, with the support of the dark cults. That\'s how the war began.";
D.q[2985] = "Perfect! Make sure you remember it. This information is priceless.";
D.q[490] = "No one ever told you not to rob a thief? You don\'t have enough Kamas, there is nothing I can do for you.";
D.q[1956] = "We would need to either contact them directly or find out where to meet them. And stop all this robbery. That will be difficult... hum!";
D.q[313] = "There\'s no point in closing my eyes, the Ghetto Raid potion is a resounding failure. Gotta pull myself together if I want to avoid bankruptcy.";
D.q[3570] = "Sometimes, when I wake up, I notice that I\'m still asleep! This can last for a long time. I can talk, walk, work, even go for a nap... but I\'m asleep. A useful talent, don\'t you think - since I\'m always resting, I\'m exceptionally strong. My name is Djaycy Awooare - I can be aware even when I\'m asleep, get it?";
D.q[3129] = "Perfect! You\'ve got the 50 Kaliptus leaves and flowers I need for my herbal tea!";
D.q[3084] = "As you know, I\'m a professional smuggler. King Allister outlawed the sale of aphrodisiacs and Bootlicker Potions. I think he\'s just afraid of having a heart attack in front of all his courtesans... or maybe he just doesn\'t want to exempt any more merchants from their taxes.";
D.q[566] = "Hm, you closer, me no see you!";
D.q[1639] = "You should go to your class temple to increase your knowledge. The Weapon Master will teach you some new techniques and will certainly have a few missions to entrust you with.";
D.q[2679] = "Prayers are good. Offerings are best! By the way, the goddess frowns when she mentions your name. Are you sure you\'ve been a good disciple? Hum... I know! To be accepted as one of her disciples, you should offer her one of those drinks... you know... the ones that make her happy...";
D.q[679] = "It\'s true that the Annex volumes of the Encyclopaedia of Alchemy cannot be found. The same goes for the new editions that should have arrived here. The rumour is that these precious manuscripts are discreetly stolen from under our noses. The thieves find them useful, no doubt... but for what?";
D.q[1040] = "Very good, I\'m really impressed!";
D.q[5931] = "Hello. If I hid my emotions away, it was for a good reason.\nI\'m quite tired at the moment, so if you have something to say, say it quickly.";
D.q[587] = "He! Why food here? You wait to be cook. You not pass. Only great Kanniball can!";
D.q[5469] = "Pfff, you not fun!";
D.q[4092] = "Perfect. Just one more second, here ... like this ... a little alteration here... A wonderful dress, I entrust you with it.";
D.q[2916] = "Perhaps you\'ve heard that we captured and interrogated a group of Bontarian renegades. Those rascals told our enemies about the two statuettes which symbolise good and evil in humanity. They say that Maimane gave these statuettes to Sumens and now Brakmar is looking to get them back. \nWe know now that the statuettes are linked in some way or another to the Terra family. Setag, the master of the Enutrofs must surely know something about it. Go and see him.";
D.q[1528] = "Pff... we didn\'t even have time to have fun with those weaklings.";
D.q[5697] = "Pff, as if I was going to cry about a piece of cutlery like that!";
D.q[613] = "May the Gods of Amakna bless you, my son! What kind of miracle guided you to this modest but divine place?";
D.q[3313] = "Where will I be able to find nice Dragoturkeys for the King Allister?";
D.q[1405] = "Where are the seeds I gave you? Well, you\'ll have to pay 1,000 Kamas if you want some more!";
D.q[6160] = "I\'ve written everything you need to know to catch a monster\'s soul in your journal. You should get to Pandala. I hope you don\'t mind travelling.";
D.q[3936] = "Phew, I\'ve never worked so hard! I had to carry jute bags from Lily\'s boat to the castle! Besides, I\'m parched...";
D.q[3461] = "I\'m talking about the one which says that the Bworks have a library with giant stills that pump out Bwork beer. They must have hidden the recipe somewhere.";
D.q[618] = "He asked me the circumstances of the death. Considering the situation I answered and explained to him that a detail caught my eyes during the autopsy. In fact, a number was inscribed on each of the victim\'s front teeth.";
D.q[620] = "Hello,\nWhat can I, Uba Tesse, alchemist of alchemists do for you?";
D.q[2442] = "Our lands are populated with the most fascinating creatures. You should go into the wilderness to find the local flora and fauna and to improve your zoological and botanical knowledge. Heartfelt and pure intentions are usually enough to cajole them.";
D.q[2017] = "Plain wood, not even carved, no detail? It\'s depressing! Well look now kid, I\'m going to slip you some good wood.";
D.q[2578] = "I can tell from your look that you\'ve come to help us! Ah yes, news travels fast in Pandala! All my Pandawas are busy at the moment and I need someone I can trust to bring those Bamboos to the Shield Smith.";
D.q[3710] = "Piwi piwi piwi?";
D.q[7541] = "Which Doploons do you want to exchange?";
D.q[7540] = "Which Doploons do you want to exchange?";
