D.q[4052] = "Pnj(893) et Message(4051)";
D.q[2637] = "Poochan? Poochan... Here is the little Pandawette! But it\'s a girl! True, anything can happen in Pandala... Akane might get upset... I\'m sorry, I can\'t. I\'m leaving it up to Akane. Sort it out with her!";
D.q[2615] = "Poochan feel better. You turn. Take it. Drink a bit of Bow Meow source and look for a person scared of you. If you find, you tell Poochan.";
D.q[7542] = "Which Doploons do you want to exchange?";
D.q[1918] = "Welcome to my humble shop, I sell very few things here, but I spend most of my time training apprentices. My creations are unique and most often only made to order.";
D.q[6446] = "You dare to lie to me? You know what we do to insubordinates around here. That Gobball was getting very hungry...";
D.q[254] = "Confronting me in a duel is a privilege I only grant members of my class. When facing others, I only unsheathe to kill.";
D.q[5534] = "Praise be to Silvosse! Praise to the little Dreggon that he taught to fly. I am eternally greatful and I am certain that the God Osamodas has taken notice of your actions. \nI can teach you no more. It\'s time you take your first steps in Bonta alone.";
D.q[702] = "I see you already master curative meditation. There\'s nothing else I can teach you.\nYou should be able to cope alone from now on.";
D.q[1885] = "All my metaria and runes have disappeared. Argh! Bloody robbers! Why me? Why today of all days? What am I going to do? I promised my date I\'d show them to her... I don\'t have time to get them back...";
D.q[3425] = "Have you seen my children? They\'re a pair of brats!";
D.q[1297] = "WHAT? Over my dead body!";
D.q[5498] = "Praise be to Silvosse! Praise to the little Dreggon that he taught to fly. I am eternally greatful and I am certain that the Goddess Feca has taken notice of your actions. \nI can teach you no more. It\'s time you take your first steps in Bonta alone.";
D.q[3300] = "Which book shall I read when I\'m at the library? The Dragon Era? The Dragoturkey Handbook?";
D.q[930] = "Are ya the one who made a mess of my littl\' bro\'s face? Have a try at that with me and you\'ll see...";
D.q[996] = "But how did you manage to get in here?";
D.q[5537] = "Praise be to Silvosse! Praise to the little Dreggon that he taught to fly. I am eternally greatful and I am certain that the Goddess Xelor has taken notice of your actions. \nI can teach you no more. It\'s time you take your first steps in Bonta alone.";
D.q[3235] = "Don\'t take advantage of my generosity. You\'re rich enough already.\nYiiiihooooo hooooo...";
D.q[1148] = "Here, give this to your master, he should be delighted.\nAnd advise him to protect his rear end, some of my disciples aren\'t too fond of him, mmmwahaha!";
D.q[5077] = "Prepare youself a little, things may get dangerous. Come back and see me when you\'re finished and I\'ll take you over there.";
D.q[4077] = "Which spell do you want to unlearn?";
D.q[3815] = "Heeeeyyy, didn\'t I say you\'d go far. Now, listen close kid... If you lose this dungeon key, and you should really try not to lose it, but if you do, or even if you wanna go back to the dungeon for a second look, you can find these keys. How? Well, the wild animals round these part just love eating adventurers. Some adventurers have the dungeon keys on them when they get eaten. So if you need a new key, just kill as many creatures as you can and you\'ll find one eventually. Got it?";
D.q[3914] = "I know most of the ladies and gentlemen at the court. None of them is worthy of the Prince, but that\'s just my opinion.";
D.q[4079] = "Which spell do you want to unlearn?";
D.q[1369] = "Hmm, let me work in peace.";
D.q[1569] = "Pwaaf! Take my deeds and never come back.";
D.q[5965] = "Putting up with Djaul is a tough cross to bear.";
D.q[4081] = "Which spell do you want to unlearn?";
D.q[1425] = "Back already? I thought Danathor would give you a mission... but if you have some free time, ask the cook, he needs ingredients for tonight\'s dinner.";
D.q[1424] = "Doh! My ring!";
D.q[1428] = "Hemm, it seems you found the culprit. I\'ll wait for the other officers\' reports. And in the meantime, I\'ll keep an eye on this character!";
D.q[1300] = "Raahhh! Go away, you and your money! And tell Oto that from today on, I\'ll no longer give him credit!";
D.q[1511] = "Are you sure? If you refuse to talk to me, it means you\'re rising up against one of the leaders of Brakmar.";
D.q[3040] = "Rargh! I feel weak! I don\'t have much energy left! This fight could have been my last one... And I don\'t even have a healing potion with me... Hehe, luckily enough I\'ve got some initiative and I sorted it out!";
D.q[4416] = "Really? Aie, I\'m so scared... I\'m shaking. Are you really going to hurt me if I don\'t cooperate?";
D.q[2689] = "I\'m the best Pandawaiian shield smith in the world! I defy my apprentices to overpass me. That\'s the best way to progress for them as well as for me. Remember that!";
D.q[2124] = "My name\'s Louc.";
D.q[2206] = "Really? Too bad, you don\'t know what you\'re missing.";
D.q[6580] = "Really? You want me to come help your troops in their manoeuvres? With pleasure! Get me out of here and take me to your boss. As far as I can see, there\'s only two groups between us and the exit. \nAh no, here come the Ribs. They must have followed us here. I\'ll let you take care of them, I\'m far too tired to tackle them.";
D.q[1409] = "Reeeaally straange, iit doeesn\'t taalllyy wiith thee infooormaatiioon giiveen by thee gaaards. Yoouu daaree liiee before a Braakmaariaann ccouurt? I haave no uuse foor deemons whoo doon\'t resspeect thhe ruuuules, geet oout oof heeree!";
D.q[1896] = "Could you visit the suspicious places? Analyse the pebbles, make a little description and bring me the results. I\'ve got 3 places to start with. The first is at the southern end of the village. The second is on the northern path to the forest. And the third leads to the caves. You\'ll find them easily... just go north and take a right at the crossroads.";
D.q[2897] = "I must take care of the level passage of many others enthusiasts. Try to come back in two hours, at least!";
D.q[5137] = "Rogue Inkgo is in the middle of questioning.";
D.q[1820] = "I promised my sons to bring them small twiggy swords. But it seems somebody emptied the supply of the temple before I did. If you bring me back one of these swords, I\'ll let you fight a Dopple...";
D.q[6058] = "Rosal has to join us, we\'re the ones who protect this world against Evil. The members of the Order of the Valiant Heart fight and sometimes die for our principles. Without us the world would tumble into the darkness of anarchy and no hope would be left.";
D.q[6223] = "I worked for Xephires for three years before taking over my mother\'s jewellers shop. At that time Xephires was just getting started in the world of business and things were difficult for the both of us.";
D.q[5418] = "Ruth Banke? I haven\'t seen that rascal in weeks. If you see him, tell him he better pay me back soon - my patience has its limits you know.";
D.q[6113] = "Well, you are motivated, that\'s for sure. You are loyal to Bonta, and you proved that by taking risks for your Order. I am proud to welcome you into the ranks of the Legenday Heroes. All the same, the Tower of Gisgoul is still standing despite the Grande Fée d\'Artifice Hille, but that\'s another story.";
D.q[1748] = "Sacriers are very resistant characters, they\'re always looking for things to help increase their lifespan.";
D.q[2326] = "Houmpf! Niark Grrrrrroahr:";
D.q[2477] = "It\'s so sad to see all those bamboos splitting... But without any Amber, there\'s nothing we can do about it!";
D.q[2328] = "Boohoo! *She holds back a big sob!*";
D.q[5702] = "Sacrilege! You have the brains of a Trool and the IQ of a Blop! You\'re crazy, destroying those beautiful jewels like that. And for what? Some information of trifling significance. You really are evil incarnate.";
D.q[1749] = "Sadidas are very strong or intelligent characters. They\'re always looking for things to help them get stronger and smarter.";
D.q[2079] = "Say! We give the Enutrofs a hand in their search, and all that we get in the end is some sick animals. And not any kind of sickness! The kind we\'re not able to cure by ourselves! Fortunately, we can rely on the Eniripsas...";
D.q[5800] = "Salutations. I asked you for 10 blue larva skins, I hope you\'ve brought them for me.";
D.q[6575] = "Salutations. Amayiro sent you to sort out our difficulty with manoeuvres, did he?";
D.q[2454] = "Say, what a rude guy! You must have had a tough time, but the reward is worth it.";
D.q[2989] = "Seriously, where do you come from? A Bwork\'s backside? Just have a look around you.... We are in an Inn. This is the right place to find beer, isn\'t it? All you need to do is to go to this tall hefty bloke over there, you know, the Inn keeper. Usually this type of bloke loves to sell beer.... (sigh).";
D.q[3548] = "See, that wasn\'t too hard, was it. Get all the practice you can, for only the best receive the blessing of their god.";
D.q[3373] = "It\'s no easy task, but keep your eyes on that vision that awaits you... Metamunch\'s. Enough to spur a turnip into cold-blooded slaughter.";
D.q[2363] = "Patrol, patrol, they said! That was nearly the end of us, bloody hell!";
D.q[6317] = "Set that box down here, I\'ll take care of it right away and then prepare a report for your boss.";
D.q[5505] = "Seven allies from the same faction.\nAn eight to get to the bottom.\nAngelic or demonic wings\nA tough battle with the elements.\nThe most precious of materials.";
D.q[3082] = "She wants more? These Enutrofs really earn their bad reputation. Here\'s another 1,000 Kamas. Hurry back for your reward. ";
D.q[3653] = "She lives just a little north of here.";
D.q[3854] = "Shall I go on?";
D.q[6599] = "She\'s critically ill, it won\'t be easy to save her. I just hope we\'re not too late.\n...\nI\'ve done my best, but the results aren\'t conclusive. What have you done to her, she looks like she\'s been passed down through ten generations of Bworkettes. You\'d better take better care of Sadida\'s creations in future, or the god will start losing his patience with you.";
D.q[1525] = "About ten I said! Otherwise they\'re useless. You\'ll have to go back there!";
D.q[6783] = "Shh, not so loud. This is a library, not the Bagrutte Inn. I can only see four solutions. The first - reunite the six primordial Dofus. With that much power in your hands you\'d have no problem releasing the Bwork mage from his unhappy state. \nThe second is to invoke the demon of the 666th circle and to make a pact with him. Unfortunately I don\'t know what such a pact would entail, so you\'ll have to find him and discuss it with him yourself.\nThe third solution is to empty the Asse sea in less than three days, which is almost impossible, obviously. The last possibility is a ritual which consists of travelling around the Cania Plains in eighty days on one hand... blindfold. I don\'t need to tell you that you cannot change hands once you\'ve set off. \nIf it comes to it, I suppose you could always try to sort things out by making a clothes peg and... ahhh, sorry, forget what I just said.";
D.q[403] = "Shhh!";
D.q[5567] = "Great! You got here in time to stop the fields being contaminated. I\'m very pleased with you. \nI\'ve promoted you to Spy, and something tells me it won\'t be long before I\'ll need you again.\nHere\'s 1,000 Kamas for your trouble. By the way, how did it go with Fidji Merline?";
D.q[4413] = "Wonderful. We\'ve finally captured that rascal. It\'s a pity that his Bontarian contact can\'t be found... Well, thanks for your help and motivation. I asked the baker to give me the best breads so we can celebrate this in style... you\'re welcome to take a few! As for the two prisoner, well, they\'ll be questions and I\'ll make sure that Xephires\' riches are distributed among the people.";
D.q[3155] = "Shush! Be quiet! You\'re in a library here! You know, if you want to open your mind, you have to shut your trap. That\'s called wisdom, child. Now be quiet!!!";
